issues.body:
Some AS might need to interact with the user solely for routing inputs (choose your Bank, choose your University, etc).
Such interactions using html are undesired as they:
- Break the browser-less flow.
- Can't share remembered choices made on browser (cookie), with client app

Currently it's declared as an unsupported case.
Perhaps AS requiring routing choice can provide app a JSON document using the content-type: **application/vnd.oauth.app2app.routing+json;** 


```

{
  // logo of AS
  "logo":"uri or base64-encoded logo",
  // Pre-defined selection, usually a drop down select box
  "options": {
    // request param name is "city" for this option
    "city": {
      "title": "Location",
      "description": "Choose the city in you work",
      "hint": "Enter your email",
      "values": {
        "berlin": { "name": "Berlin", "logo": "uri or base64-encoded logo" },
        "madrid": { "name": "Madrid", "logo": "uri or base64-encoded logo"  }
      }
    },
    // request param name is "department" for this option
    "department": {
      "title": "Department",
      "description": "Choose your department",
      "hint": "Enter your email",
      "values": {
        "d123": "Finance",
        "d456": "IT"
      }
    }
    // ...
  },
  // Free text inputs
  "inputs": {
    // request param name is "username" for this input field
    "email": { "hint": "Enter your email", "title": "E-Mail", "description": "Lore Ipsum" }
    // ...
  },
  // Response must have either
  "post": "url to POST to using application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
  // or
  "get": "url to use for a GET with query params"
  // not both
}

```

The body shall instruct on the options, how to display them (name, logo) and how to respond.
The response should provide a cookie to denote the session

This enables client to present routing options to end-user and provide the decisions to AS.
